From: Mathieu Desnoyers <mathieu.desnoyers@efficios.com>
Date: Thu, 13 May 2010 19:28:09 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 326/391] lttng-assign-reader-page-to-first-initially

lttng assign reader page to first initially

Signed-off-by: Mathieu Desnoyers <mathieu.desnoyers@polymtl.ca>
---
 ltt/ltt-relay-alloc.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/ltt/ltt-relay-alloc.c b/ltt/ltt-relay-alloc.c
index b6377f2..dfef18b 100644
--- a/ltt/ltt-relay-alloc.c
+++ b/ltt/ltt-relay-alloc.c
@@ -91,7 +91,7 @@ int ltt_chanbuf_allocate(struct ltt_chanbuf_alloc *buf, size_t size,
 		if (unlikely(!buf->buf_rsb.pages))
 			goto free_buf_wsb;
 	} else {
-		buf->buf_rsb.pages = NULL;
+		buf->buf_rsb.pages = buf->buf_wsb[0].pages;
 	}
 
 	/* Assign pages to write-side page index */
